{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, in few-shot learning, the model learns from the demonstrations available (i.e., few-shot text prompts).",
    "Among the most popular LLMs, BERT (Devlin et al., 2019), GPT-3 (Brown et al., 2020), GPT-3.5 foot_2, GPT-4 foot_3, and T5 (Raffel et al., 2020) deserve attention.",
    "BERT (Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers) was released by Google in October 2018 (slightly after GTP-1 dated June 2018).",
    "It is a pre-trained transformer-based encoder model that can be fine-tuned on specific NLP tasks such as named entity recognition (NER), question answering, and sentence classification.",
    "Moreover, GPT-3, GPT-3.5, and GPT-4 (generative pre-trained transformer) models were released by OpenAI in 2020, 2022, and 2023, respectively."
  ]
}